strings.Value: "And still — how do great empires decay? How does their fall begin? This is a mystery worthy of a great mind..."
"The cyclopes were destroyed by cruelty. And debauchery."
"In the north, every fool knows the answer. The end is near when a great chief who has conquered all the neighboring tribes, starts to eat more than hunt and sleep more than fight."
"That's simple — someone gets used to blabbing and stops keeping their eyes open, ha ha ha hmm..."
